49:56.327 --> 49:58.294
- [Binschii] I never
knew her name,

49:58.296 --> 50:00.396
but she was the first
girl I ever loved.

50:05.236 --> 50:07.670
I remember her
face 'til this day.

50:10.341 --> 50:11.741
- Hey, you sit!

50:19.350 --> 50:21.417
(door knocking loudly)

50:21.419 --> 50:23.119
- Come in, Hiram.

50:35.800 --> 50:37.299
What are we gonna call him?

50:39.103 --> 50:41.704
He looks like a Silas

50:43.174 --> 50:45.041
or a Simon.

50:46.110 --> 50:47.777
What do you think, Hiram?

50:47.779 --> 50:50.079
- We already have a Simon.

50:50.515 --> 50:52.314
- That's right.

50:52.316 --> 50:54.683
Silas it is.

50:54.685 --> 50:58.454
Silas, I am Mrs. Braxton.

51:00.725 --> 51:03.159
This is Mr. Hiram.

51:09.200 --> 51:12.334
There you go,
let's get this off.

51:13.805 --> 51:16.105
Oh, look at this hair.

51:18.443 --> 51:20.109
- He had this knife on him.

51:22.413 --> 51:24.113
- He did, did he?

51:24.816 --> 51:27.083
My little Indian warrior.

51:29.353 --> 51:30.553
D'you bring the scissors?

51:32.857 --> 51:35.224
- Ma'am, I forgot them.

51:37.862 --> 51:38.828
- Well?

51:47.405 --> 51:49.405
Stand still, Silas.

51:50.174 --> 51:55.511
Let the burdens be upon
the Lord. (chuckles)

