(Mrs. Braxton humming)

52:45.897 --> 52:48.330
(soft piano music)
(birds chirping)

52:48.332 --> 52:50.299
- Sometimes I ask the Lord

52:52.236 --> 52:54.403
where all the goodness
is in this world.

52:58.476 --> 53:01.377
That's what I always
admired in you, John Towne;

53:03.314 --> 53:04.313
your goodness.

53:06.484 --> 53:08.284
You have a kind heart.

53:10.588 --> 53:12.588
One day I think people
will look back in shame

53:12.590 --> 53:14.390
at how we treated the Indians.

53:17.929 --> 53:20.930
Now you go get that boy
and you take him home.

53:23.234 --> 53:25.234
You just make sure
you come back to me.

53:27.872 --> 53:29.205
- I will.

53:30.274 --> 53:32.341
- I'll be waitin'.

53:40.284 --> 53:41.617
- [John] I felt whole again.

53:42.987 --> 53:45.621
I wondered why I had wasted
a lifetime without her.

53:47.892 --> 53:49.525
That was behind me now.

53:50.561 --> 53:53.229
I would spend the rest of
my days with Maggie Butler.

53:56.500 --> 53:58.500
- [Maggie] As I
watched him ride off,

53:59.704 --> 54:01.971
this time I knew he
would come back for me.

54:04.475 --> 54:05.441
- He ain't dead.

54:07.311 --> 54:08.477
- You just said he was dead.

54:08.479 --> 54:10.279
- No, O'Toole is dead.

54:10.281 --> 54:11.547
Talkin' about the marshall.

54:11.549 --> 54:12.514
- What marshall?

54:12.516 --> 54:13.649
- The marshall we hung.

54:13.651 --> 54:18.921
He's in town right now walkin'
around with some Indian kid.

54:18.923 --> 54:21.457
- You look so smart.

54:22.660 --> 54:24.326
(door knocking)

54:24.328 --> 54:25.561
Come in.

54:25.563 --> 54:28.731
(soft soothing music)

54:33.337 --> 54:36.739
All we have left
is to cut the hair.

54:36.741 --> 54:40.643
When you're done, bring
him to the classroom.

54:41.646 --> 54:42.945
- Yes, ma'am.

55:06.771 --> 55:08.570
Don't you resist me, little boy.

55:09.974 --> 55:11.540
You will do as I say.

55:12.743 --> 55:18.080
I am Hiram and I run this place.

55:18.082 --> 55:19.048
Lay down.

55:23.487 --> 55:28.557
(knife stabbing)
(Hiram wincing)

55:37.735 --> 55:39.702
He stabbed me.

55:39.704 --> 55:42.638
Come back here,
you lil' heathen!

55:54.085 --> 55:58.020
(climactic orchestral music)

56:04.095 --> 56:06.329
- [Binschii] I don't
know how it happened,

56:06.330 --> 56:08.564
but there he was on his
big horse and I ran to him.

56:23.748 --> 56:26.648
Then I saw her running
like me to freedom

56:26.650 --> 56:28.484
from the Indian boarding school.

56:29.420 --> 56:31.053
She smiled as she ran.

56:40.731 --> 56:42.030
(gun blasting)

56:42.032 --> 56:43.532
Then I heard the
shot and she fell.

56:46.137 --> 56:48.737
(gun blasting)

57:15.733 --> 57:18.834
- How could you shoot a
little girl in the back?

57:18.836 --> 57:21.637
(gun blasting)

57:23.908 --> 57:27.643
(somber orchestral music)

58:05.749 --> 58:09.885
I knew they would come for
us, so we rode hard all night.

58:40.584 --> 58:43.252
In the mornin', we were
in the high country.

58:43.254 --> 58:47.189
(triumphant orchestral music)

59:16.720 --> 59:20.255
(foreboding tribal music)

1:00:22.886 --> 1:00:24.886
I could feel
somethin' around us,

1:00:26.056 --> 1:00:27.723
but I couldn't see anything.

1:00:31.662 --> 1:00:34.830
(soft soothing music)

1:00:54.418 --> 1:00:58.687
We found an old cabin and
we went inside to rest.

1:01:36.760 --> 1:01:40.162
(foreboding tribal music)

1:01:44.902 --> 1:01:48.904
These Apaches were with
Chacon and they led 'em to us.

1:02:02.753 --> 1:02:05.053
- [Binschii] I knew he wanted
me to stay in the cabin.

1:02:05.055 --> 1:02:07.456
But when he fell asleep,
I slipped outside.

1:02:12.129 --> 1:02:14.096
I just wanted to be a kid again.

1:02:16.066 --> 1:02:19.000
(birds chirping)

1:02:20.471 --> 1:02:23.138
Then it happened, I
was in the big arms

1:02:23.140 --> 1:02:25.040
of the man that
murdered my father.

1:02:27.044 --> 1:02:29.411
- [John] I don't
know what woke me.

1:02:29.413 --> 1:02:31.913
But when I awoke, I
had a sense of dread

1:02:31.915 --> 1:02:34.816
and the little boy was
nowhere to be seen.

1:02:34.818 --> 1:02:38.920
(somber orchestral music)

1:02:38.922 --> 1:02:40.956
(arrow whooshing)
(John wincing)

1:02:40.958 --> 1:02:43.158
An arrow in the shoulder
is all I remember,

1:02:44.428 --> 1:02:46.428
then the world went
dark very quickly.

1:02:47.531 --> 1:02:50.232
(John thudding)

1:03:07.117 --> 1:03:10.819
- [Binschii] I remember thinking
that this truly was the end

1:03:10.821 --> 1:03:12.454
as we rode into the forest.

1:03:13.991 --> 1:03:19.060
(fire crackling)
(frogs croaking)

1:03:23.200 --> 1:03:26.568
(men laughing)
(muffled crosstalk)

1:03:26.570 --> 1:03:28.036
That night, they were drinking

1:03:28.038 --> 1:03:31.173
and more Apaches seeped
in from the darkness.

1:03:46.190 --> 1:03:49.157
The man that murdered my
father was givin' them rifles.

1:03:53.297 --> 1:03:57.499
(men speaking foreign language)

1:04:09.146 --> 1:04:12.147
They yell and scream and fought.

1:04:12.149 --> 1:04:15.517
(men drunken shouting)

1:04:21.058 --> 1:04:23.191
I couldn't stop looking at
my grandfather's necklace

1:04:23.193 --> 1:04:24.993
around that big man's neck.

1:04:25.863 --> 1:04:31.066
(muffled crosstalk)
(fire crackling)

1:04:41.945 --> 1:04:45.080
Then some of the Apaches
left with the rifles.

1:04:45.082 --> 1:04:48.016
(hooves clopping)

1:05:08.972 --> 1:05:11.539
After the rest fell
asleep, he took me.

1:05:11.541 --> 1:05:14.059
I thought to kill
me, but instead

1:05:14.060 --> 1:05:16.578
we went into a dark mineshaft
where he hid his treasure.

1:05:23.654 --> 1:05:25.287
- [John] It was
dark when I woke.

1:05:27.057 --> 1:05:29.991
I snapped the arrow and
pulled it outta my body.

1:05:29.993 --> 1:05:35.063
(arrow snapping)
(John wincing)

1:05:35.933 --> 1:05:38.133
Then I ran all night
followin' their tracks.

1:05:39.202 --> 1:05:43.071
(adventurous western music)

1:05:55.252 --> 1:05:57.719
In the mornin', I found
'em camped in a meadow

1:05:57.721 --> 1:06:00.622
with their horses nearby
huddled up together in a bunch.

1:06:14.237 --> 1:06:17.439
It was an easy thing
to get them goin'.

1:06:19.309 --> 1:06:24.379
(intense orchestral music)
(hooves stomping)

1:06:33.724 --> 1:06:36.391
- [Bandit] Where the horses run?

1:06:37.394 --> 1:06:40.195
(gun blasting)

1:06:58.315 --> 1:07:03.318
(gun blasting)
(bullets pinging)

1:07:32.249 --> 1:07:33.281
(gun blasting)
(Culpepper groaning)

1:07:33.283 --> 1:07:36.251
(river trickling)

1:08:09.719 --> 1:08:14.355
(gun blasting)
(birds chirping)

1:08:14.357 --> 1:08:17.125
- You just won't die, will you?

1:08:18.361 --> 1:08:19.327
You throw that
pistol over the edge

1:08:19.329 --> 1:08:21.229
or I'll snap this boy's neck.

1:08:49.359 --> 1:08:50.325
- [John] I was too
weak from the arrow

1:08:50.327 --> 1:08:52.260
to put up much of a fight.

1:08:52.262 --> 1:08:57.332
(intense western music)
(John wincing)

1:09:04.207 --> 1:09:06.875
(fist thudding)

1:09:23.193 --> 1:09:25.460
- Marshall, think you can fly?

1:09:26.363 --> 1:09:29.264
(knife stabbing)

1:09:32.302 --> 1:09:35.470
(tribal guitar music)

1:09:41.444 --> 1:09:44.412
(Chacon shouting)

1:09:50.587 --> 1:09:51.853
- [Binschii] Before
we left his place,

1:09:51.855 --> 1:09:53.454
I showed him the mineshaft.

1:09:54.457 --> 1:09:56.291
- Let's see what's in here.

1:10:00.964 --> 1:10:02.430
Oh wow.

1:10:12.609 --> 1:10:16.277
I had never been a rich
man until that moment.

1:10:16.279 --> 1:10:19.214
(John chuckling)

1:10:29.259 --> 1:10:34.329
(birds chirping)
(soft serene music)

1:11:37.927 --> 1:11:41.562
(intense foreboding music)

1:11:58.381 --> 1:12:00.448
- Is that them?
- Yeah.

1:12:01.451 --> 1:12:04.986
Do what you want with the
boy, but the marshall's mine.

1:12:04.988 --> 1:12:06.487
All mine.

1:12:06.489 --> 1:12:08.489
- I'm gonna take that
little Indian boy's scalp

1:12:08.491 --> 1:12:09.791
and feed it to my pups.

1:12:12.696 --> 1:12:15.663
(hooves stomping)

1:12:21.004 --> 1:12:23.004
- [John] I had my
pick as they rode in.

1:12:24.574 --> 1:12:26.341
I shot Roy first.

1:12:27.677 --> 1:12:29.010
(rifle blasting)
(Roy wincing)

1:12:29.012 --> 1:12:30.545
I figured he would
be my biggest threat

1:12:30.547 --> 1:12:32.747
since the sheriff
would be reckless

1:12:32.749 --> 1:12:35.550
'cause he wanted revenge
for me shootin' his woman.

1:12:37.020 --> 1:12:40.421
I shot Roy in the gut for how
he was rough with the boy.

1:12:40.423 --> 1:12:45.493
(rifle blasting)
(soft foreboding music)

1:12:51.101 --> 1:12:53.835
(rifle blasting)

1:13:02.145 --> 1:13:05.079
(rifle blasting)

1:13:08.718 --> 1:13:13.788
(guns blasting)
(intense western music)

1:13:33.743 --> 1:13:35.576
- Oh god, my shoulder!

1:13:35.578 --> 1:13:36.677
Ow, my shoulder!

1:13:38.448 --> 1:13:39.414
God.

1:13:41.184 --> 1:13:42.550
- Don't shoot no more.

1:13:42.552 --> 1:13:44.552
Please don't shoot.
- Ow, my shoulder.

1:13:45.488 --> 1:13:46.454
Help!

1:13:48.057 --> 1:13:50.725
My shoulder.
- Don't shoot!

1:13:52.529 --> 1:13:55.163
- My shoulder!
- Get up.

1:13:56.900 --> 1:13:58.599
Where ya hit?
- My shoulder.

1:13:58.601 --> 1:13:59.834
Help, my shoulder.

1:13:59.836 --> 1:14:00.768
I'm shot.

1:14:02.105 --> 1:14:05.473
Ow, my shoulder.
- Don't shoot, please.

1:14:09.646 --> 1:14:11.746
- Come out here to
kill a boy, did you?

1:14:11.748 --> 1:14:13.581
What's wrong with you?!

1:14:13.583 --> 1:14:16.717
How 'bout I just blow you
to kingdom come right now?

1:14:18.755 --> 1:14:21.756
Now you with your left hand,
you take that gun outta there

1:14:21.758 --> 1:14:23.691
and you throw it over there.

1:14:23.693 --> 1:14:24.926
You look at me now!
- My shoulder.

1:14:24.928 --> 1:14:26.127
- You see me?

1:14:26.129 --> 1:14:26.928
You throw it.

1:14:27.931 --> 1:14:30.198
Now you, stand up son!

1:14:30.200 --> 1:14:31.732
- Yes, sir.
- Be a man.

1:14:34.904 --> 1:14:36.204
Now you stay here,
you understand me?

1:14:36.206 --> 1:14:37.805
You don't move.

1:14:37.807 --> 1:14:39.774
Say yes, sir!
- Yes, sir.

1:14:42.745 --> 1:14:45.713
(sheriff wincing)

1:14:51.788 --> 1:14:52.820
- You bastard.

1:15:00.163 --> 1:15:01.629
- Look at me, sheriff.

1:15:03.900 --> 1:15:06.834
(rifle blasting)

1:15:17.847 --> 1:15:18.880
Is he kin to you?

1:15:23.853 --> 1:15:26.254
You tell me why I shouldn't
kill you right now.

1:15:27.657 --> 1:15:28.623
Tell me why.

1:15:29.259 --> 1:15:30.191
Speak up, son!

1:15:30.193 --> 1:15:33.761
- We're young.
- Yeah, you're young.

1:15:37.667 --> 1:15:40.801
- I tell you what,
get on 'em horses.

1:15:41.871 --> 1:15:44.305
If I see you back
here, I will kill you.

1:15:44.307 --> 1:15:46.774
You bring your uncle,
I'll kill your uncle.

1:15:46.776 --> 1:15:48.843
You understand me?
- Yes, sir.

1:15:48.845 --> 1:15:49.810
- Now git!

1:16:00.957 --> 1:16:03.891
(hooves stomping)

1:16:07.897 --> 1:16:09.230
You better get, boy!

1:16:22.045 --> 1:16:25.613
(soothing piano music)

1:16:43.666 --> 1:16:46.734
(soft serene music)

1:17:28.044 --> 1:17:31.646
(soothing piano music)

1:17:41.791 --> 1:17:44.959
(serene tribal music)

1:18:09.886 --> 1:18:12.887
I gave the boy some gold,
and jewels and some green backs.

1:18:13.923 --> 1:18:17.024
I figured it would set him
up right in the future.

1:18:17.026 --> 1:18:18.693
It was the least I could do.

1:18:24.333 --> 1:18:28.736
- [Binschii] It felt good to
be in my land, Navajo land.

1:18:28.738 --> 1:18:32.006
(soft orchestral music)

1:18:50.993 --> 1:18:53.728
- [John] This Navajo land,
was beautiful country.

1:18:54.297 --> 1:18:56.931
Some of the most beautiful
country I've ever seen.

1:19:24.994 --> 1:19:28.229
(soothing piano music)

1:19:43.446 --> 1:19:46.514
We have been through
a lot together.

1:19:51.854 --> 1:19:53.854
I was gonna miss this boy.

1:19:53.856 --> 1:19:55.222
He was like a son to me now.

1:20:00.530 --> 1:20:03.097
- [Binschii] It was hard
sayin' goodbye to this man.

1:20:07.570 --> 1:20:11.572
I would always remember him
surrounded by the wind and sand.

1:20:11.574 --> 1:20:13.474
Like in my grandfather's story,

1:20:13.476 --> 1:20:15.176
this time it was a good wind.

1:20:16.946 --> 1:20:20.147
I often wonder if my grandfather
had sent this man to me.

1:20:21.217 --> 1:20:24.285
I guess I will never know,
but I'm glad I knew him.

1:20:26.055 --> 1:20:28.489
- [John] It gave me great
joy to see him home.

1:20:35.965 --> 1:20:37.865
(Binschii speaking
foreign language)

1:20:37.867 --> 1:20:40.968
(serene vocal music)

1:20:49.178 --> 1:20:54.281
- [Binschii] I was home
in the arms of my mother.

1:21:11.100 --> 1:21:14.235
(somber piano music)

1:21:21.177 --> 1:21:22.877
I never saw him again.

1:21:52.642 --> 1:21:56.043
(Spanish guitar music)
